DANCER and entertainer Zodwa Wabantu recently found herself in the firing line. This after the talented media personality shared a video of herself embracing and kissing her fans during her recent appearance at a club in Soshanguve, north of Tshwane. In the video, Zodwa, who is currently shooting the second season of her reality show, can be seen dancing on stage and holding hands with her fans, before she kneels down to go and kiss them. It did not take long for the video to go viral after it was shared and for her fans to question her whether she had forgotten that we are in the middle of a pandemic. ALSO READ |HIT SONG JOHN VULI GATE GOES VIRAL Concerned fans commented on the viral video and asked whether the coronavirus is a thing of the past while some advised her to stop kissing her fans on the mouth. “There is no more corona?” a fan questioned the star. While another fan commented and said she knows that Zodwa loves her fans but she must be careful and she should not kiss them on the mouth: “Zodwa I love how you love your fans, but please don’t kiss them on the mouth!” While some fans were left confused by the video as we are still following Covid-19 regulations, they questioned whether they missed the memo. “Covid-19’s over or am I missing something?” a fan said. A post shared by zodwalibram (@zodwalibram) on Oct 18, 2020 at 9:32am PDT 